1 Visualization 1: Exercise solutions

1.1 Load packages and set theme

Let’s first load the packages that we need for this chapter.

library("knitr") # for rendering the RMarkdown file
library("tidyverse") # for data wrangling

Let’s set the plotting theme.

theme_set(
  theme_classic()+ #set the theme 
    theme(text = element_text(size = 20)) #set the default text size
)

1.2 Practice plot 1

Make a scatter plot that shows the relationship between the variables depth (on the x-axis), and table (on the y-axis). Take a look at the description for the diamonds dataset so you know what these different variables mean. Your plot should look like the one shown in Figure 1.1.

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x = depth, y = table)) +
  geom_point()

include_graphics("figures/practice_plot1.png")

Figure 1.1: Practice plot 1.

1.3 Practice plot 2

Make a bar plot that shows the average price of diamonds (on the y-axis) as a function of their clarity (on the x-axis). Also add error bars. Your plot should look like the one shown in Figure 1.2.

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x = clarity, y = price)) +
  stat_summary(fun.y = "mean", geom = "bar") +
  stat_summary(fun.data = "mean_cl_boot", geom = "linerange")

include_graphics("figures/practice_plot2.png")

Figure 1.2: Practice plot 2.

1.4 Practice plot 3

Recreate the plot shown in Figure 1.3.

# make practice plot 3 here
ggplot(diamonds, aes(x = color, y = price, group = clarity, color = clarity)) +
  stat_summary(fun.data = "mean_cl_boot", geom = "linerange", size = 1) +
  stat_summary(fun.y = "mean", geom = "line", size = 2)

include_graphics("figures/practice_plot3.png")

Figure 1.3: Practice plot 3.

1.4.0.1 Practice plot 4

Recreate the plot shown in Figure 1.4.

# make practice plot 4 here
ggplot(diamonds, aes(x = color, y = price, fill = cut)) +
  stat_summary(fun.y = "mean",
               geom = "bar",
               position = position_dodge(width = 0.9),
               color = "black") +
  stat_summary(fun.data = "mean_cl_boot",
               geom = "linerange",
               position = position_dodge(width = 0.9),
               color = "black") +
  facet_grid(rows = vars(clarity)) +
  theme(axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10))
Warning: Removed 5 rows containing missing values (geom_linerange).

include_graphics("figures/practice_plot4.png")

Figure 1.4: Practice plot 4.
